    • createQueryString

      public String createQueryString(String query, String[] queryParameters, String databaseKey, boolean useCache, int modificationTypeIndex, VisualizationType visualizationTypeIndex, String[] visualizationParameters, boolean save)
      Generates a query on the specified database. The query may contain placeholders that have to be replaced by the parameters.
      This is the main services entry point that should be used to generate and save queries. A placeholder is set by $placeholder$ and will be replaced by the corresponding element in the query parameters. The query parameter array has to contain the elements in the same order as they appear in the query.
      Parameters:
      query - a String containing the query
      queryParameters - the query parameters as an array of Strings that contain the content of the placeholders
      databaseKey - a String containing the database key
      useCache - if true, a cached result is returned (if available) instead of performing the query again (does only affect stored queries!)
      modificationTypeIndex - the desired modification function
      visualizationTypeIndex - the desired visualization
      visualizationParameters - an array of additional parameters for the visualization, including title, height and weight
      save - if set, the query will be saved and the return statement will be the query id.
      Returns:
      Result of the query in the requested output format or the id of the saved query
